When I was young, there was
a goose living at our house.

206
00:13:45,333 --> 00:13:47,500
One day when I came back from school,

207
00:13:47,500 --> 00:13:51,467
I found it waddling around playing in our yard.

208
00:13:51,467 --> 00:13:52,900
Pardon?

209
00:13:52,900 --> 00:13:56,733
It looked so adorable and lovely that

210
00:13:56,733 --> 00:13:59,233
I didn't even wonder

211
00:14:00,267 --> 00:14:02,333
who its owner was.

212
00:14:02,333 --> 00:14:06,800
I hid it in the backyard, just
waiting for school to end.

213
00:14:06,800 --> 00:14:09,667
All I could think about was
rushing home to play with the goose.

214
00:14:10,733 --> 00:14:12,433
Uh, Doctor...

215
00:14:12,433 --> 00:14:14,167
But,

216
00:14:14,167 --> 00:14:18,433
a few days later when I hurried home after school,

217
00:14:18,433 --> 00:14:20,096
it was lying dead.

218
00:14:20,096 --> 00:14:22,633
If I'd just looked for its owner sooner,

219
00:14:22,633 --> 00:14:25,600
my beloved goose wouldn't have died.

220
00:14:25,600 --> 00:14:27,867
The guilt haunted me for a long time.

221
00:14:29,133 --> 00:14:33,367
Maybe that's even why I became a vet.

222
00:14:34,000 --> 00:14:37,833
I'm not sure what you're trying to say...

223
00:14:40,033 --> 00:14:41,800
Genie.

224
00:14:41,800 --> 00:14:43,167
Did you steal him?

225
00:14:43,167 --> 00:14:44,567
What?

226
00:14:44,567 --> 00:14:46,700
He's not your dog, right?

227
00:14:46,700 --> 00:14:49,100
Well, that's...

228
00:14:49,100 --> 00:14:52,733
Genie needs his medical history.

229
00:14:58,067 --> 00:15:00,133
See?

230
00:15:00,133 --> 00:15:02,100
Who's his real owner?

231
00:15:02,100 --> 00:15:04,067
Why do you ask?

232
00:15:04,767 --> 00:15:06,333
Genie is

233
